    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "Rig floor cleared of all personnel",
      "Driller screwed MDDM into stump to continue circulation",
      "Well secured",
      "Investigation initiated",
      "MDDM Connection Procedure updated",
      "Written Risk Assessment updated"
    ],
    "summary": "On August 31, 2015, while performing drilling operations on the Yeti #002 well aboard the Transocean Discoverer Americas, a stand of drill pipe fell free of the rig's Modular Derrick Drilling Machine (MDDM) and laid diagonally across the derrick, coming to rest against the pipe rack. The incident resulted from improper alignment of drill pipe connections, failure to recognize the misalignment before proceeding, and premature release of the Pipe Racking System arms. No personnel, equipment, or environmental harm occurred.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Pipe Racking System shall remain around drill pipe with arms engaged until connection into stump is verified",
      "Elevators on MDDM shall remain latched around drill pipe to serve as second barrier should pipe fall free"
    ],
